Attorney%20Alex%20Spiro%20wrote%20a%20letter%20to%20California%20Gov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%2C%20urging%20him%20to%20stop%20a%20proposed%20billionaire%20tax.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESpiro%20said%20his%20clients%20would%20%26quot%3Bpermanently%20relocate%26quot%3B%20if%20the%20measure%20were%20to%20become%20law.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhile%20Spiro%20did%20not%20say%20which%20clients%20he%20was%20referencing%2C%20he%20has%20previously%20represented%20well%20known%20billionaires%20and%20celebrities.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20proposed%20billionaire%20tax%20in%20California%20has%20the%20wealthy%20threatening%20to%20flee%2C%20according%20to%20a%20letter%20written%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falex-spiro-attorney-elon-musk-jay-z-bobby-shmurda-2022-06%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epower%20lawyer%20Alex%20Spiro%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Gov.%20Gavin%20Newsom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20December%2011%20letter%20that%20was%20obtained%20by%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Spiro%20lays%20out%20his%20opposition%20to%20the%20proposed%20tax%20on%20behalf%20of%20his%20clients%2C%20whom%20he%20calls%20%26quot%3BCalifornia%20residents%20who%20would%20be%20subject%20to%20the%20proposed%20Billionaire%20Tax%20Act.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20will%20trigger%20an%20exodus%20of%20capital%20and%20innovation%20from%20California%2C%26quot%3B%20Spiro%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BOur%20clients%20have%20made%20clear%20they%20will%20permanently%20relocate%20if%20subjected%20to%20this%20tax.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20measure%20proposes%20that%20California%20residents%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-many-billionaires-world-growing-net-worth-ai-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eassets%20exceeding%20%241%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20be%20subject%20to%20a%20one-time%205%25%20tax%20on%20the%20value%20of%20their%20assets.%20If%20the%20proposal%20receives%20enough%20signatures%2C%20it%20will%20appear%20on%20the%20state%20ballot%20in%20November%202026.%20If%20passed%2C%20it%20would%20apply%20retroactively%20to%20all%20California%20residents%20as%20of%20January%201%2C%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Newsom%20has%20said%20he%20is%20against%20the%20tax%20and%20would%20%26quot%3Bfight%26quot%3B%20it%2C%20he%20would%20not%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20veto%20it%20if%20it%20were%20to%20pass%20as%20a%20ballot%20measure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20wealthy%20Californians%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeter-thiel-washington-vance-musk-trump-ramaswamy-altman-palantir-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eventure%20capitalist%20Peter%20Thiel%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Google%20cofounder%20Larry%20Page%2C%20have%20considered%20shrinking%20their%20presence%20in%20California%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2025%2F12%2F26%2Ftechnology%2Fcalifornia-wealth-tax-page-thiel.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Times%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Representatives%20for%20Page%20and%20Thiel%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider%20when%20asked%20if%20they%20were%20represented%20by%20Spiro.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20weekend%2C%20billionaire%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpalmer-luckey-america-worlds-gun-store-defense-tech-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPalmer%20Luckey%3C%2Fa%3E%20took%20to%20X%20to%20voice%20his%20opposition%20to%20the%20measure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20made%20my%20money%20from%20my%20first%20company%2C%20paid%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20taxes%20on%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Anduril%20cofounder%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BNow%20me%20and%20my%20cofounders%20have%20to%20somehow%20come%20up%20with%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20cash.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20not%20clear%20which%20clients%20the%20lawyer%20was%20referencing%20in%20his%20letter%20to%20Newsom%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falex-spiro-hourly-rate-3000-lawsuit-elon-musk-kim-kardashian-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpiro's%20client%20roster%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20past%20has%20included%20billionaires%20and%20A-listers.%20He%20has%20previously%20represented%20Kim%20Kardashian%2C%20Jay-Z%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERead%20the%20full%20letter%20below%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3ERe%3A%20Constitutional%20Concerns%20Regarding%20Proposed%20Billionaire%20Tax%20Act%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EDear%20Governor%20Newsom%3A%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EI%20represent%20California%20residents%20who%20would%20be%20subject%20to%20the%20proposed%20Billionaire%20Tax%20Act%20if%20it%20qualifies%20for%20the%20November%202026%20ballot.%20I%20write%20to%20urge%20you%20to%20work%20to%20prevent%20this%20initiative%20from%20moving%20forward.%20The%20Act%20has%20serious%20legal%20problems%20and%20would%20cause%20significant%20economic%20damage%20to%20California%20and%20the%20broader%20economy.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EFirst%2C%20and%20most%20importantly%2C%20the%20Act%20would%20be%20unconstitutional.%20Although%20the%20Act%20purports%20to%20be%20a%20tax%2C%20it%20is%20in%20reality%20an%20uncompensated%20confiscation%20of%20property.%20The%20Act%20imposes%20a%205%25%20levy%20on%20total%20accumulated%20wealth%2C%20including%20illiquid%20assets%20that%20generate%20no%20income.%20That%20is%20in%20substance%20a%20taking%20without%20just%20compensation.%20As%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20explained%20in%20Armstrong%20v.%20United%20States%2C%20the%20government%20cannot%20force%20%26quot%3Bsome%20people%20alone%20to%20bear%20public%20burdens%20which%2C%20in%20all%20fairness%20and%20justice%2C%20should%20be%20borne%20by%20the%20public%20as%20a%20whole.%26quot%3B%20364%20U.S.%2040%2C%2049%20(1960).%20The%20Act%20concentrates%20an%20extraordinary%20burden%20on%20a%20small%20group%20to%20solve%20a%20general%20revenue%20problem%E2%80%94%20exactly%20what%20the%20Constitution%20prohibits.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3ESecond%2C%20for%20the%20people%20who%20relocate%20from%20California%20in%202026%20before%20the%20November%20election%2C%20the%20Act%20would%20tax%20them%20after%20they%20have%20become%20citizens%20of%20other%20States%20and%20without%20any%20ability%20to%20vote%20on%20the%20measure.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20held%20that%20retroactive%20taxation%20cannot%20be%20%26quot%3Bharsh%20and%20oppressive.%26quot%3B%20United%20States%20v.%20Carlton%2C%20512%20U.S.%2026%2C%2030%20(1994).%20A%205%25%20levy%20on%20total%20net%20worth%20imposed%20on%20former%20residents%20who%20departed%20before%20the%20law%20was%20even%20enacted%20clearly%20meets%20that%20definition.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThird%2C%20the%20Act's%20unprecedented%20novelty%20makes%20it%20especially%20vulnerable%20to%20a%20legal%20challenge.%20California%20has%20never%20imposed%20a%20wealth%20tax%2C%20much%20less%20one%20that%20reaches%20former%20residents%20and%20that%20is%20targeted%20at%20a%20small%20group%20of%20citizens.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20closely%20scrutinizes%20unprecedented%20exercises%20of%20government%20power%20precisely%20because%20they%20lack%20historical%20precedent.%20See%20Biden%20v.%20Nebraska%2C%20600%20U.S.%20477%2C%20505%20(2023).%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20has%20not%20hesitated%20to%20invalidate%20the%20retroactive%20application%20of%20new%20taxes%2C%20even%20for%20far%20less%20extreme%20measures.%20See%20Blodgett%20v.%20Holden%2C%20275%20U.S.%20142%20(1927).%20There%20can%20be%20no%20doubt%20that%20the%20current%20Supreme%20Court%20would%20carefully%20evaluate%20a%20law%20so%20out%20of%20step%20with%20the%20American%20legal%20tradition.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EFrom%20an%20economic%20perspective%2C%20the%20Act%20creates%20two%20serious%20problems.%20First%2C%20it%20will%20trigger%20an%20exodus%20of%20capital%20and%20innovation%20from%20California.%20Our%20clients%20have%20made%20clear%20they%20will%20permanently%20relocate%20if%20subjected%20to%20this%20tax.%20They%20are%20not%20alone.%20See%20California's%20wealth-tax%20test%3A%20Have%20voters%20finally%20found%20a%20policy%20that%20the%20state's%20inherent%20economic%20strengths%20can't%20overcome%3F%2C%20Wash.%20Post%20(Nov.%2017%2C%202025)%20(opinion)%20(describing%20the%20tax%20as%20%26quot%3Balmost%20tailor-made%20to%20drive%20most%20Silicon%20Valley%20tech%20companies%20to%20Austin%2C%20Texas%26quot%3B).%20In%20other%20words%2C%20by%20passing%20this%20proposal%20California%20would%20exchange%20a%20one-time%20windfall%20for%20the%20permanent%20loss%20of%20billions%20in%20annual%20income%20taxes%2C%20capital%20gains%20taxes%2C%20property%20taxes%2C%20and%20economic%20activity.%20The%20state's%20most%20economically%20productive%20residents%20would%20take%20their%20businesses%2C%20jobs%2C%20and%20charitable%20giving%20with%20them.%20Second%2C%20the%20Act%20will%20force%20destructive%20asset%20sales.%20Our%20clients%20hold%20equity%20stakes%20in%20operating%20businesses%2C%20venture%20capital%20funds%2C%20and%20real%20estate.%20Paying%20a%205%25%20wealth%20tax%20would%20require%20massive%20forced%20liquidations%2C%20depressing%20asset%20values%20and%20triggering%20market%20instability%20that%20would%20harm%20ordinary%20investors%20whose%20retirement%20accounts%20hold%20these%20same%20investments.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EOur%20clients%20are%20prepared%20to%20mount%20a%20vigorous%20constitutional%20challenge%20if%20this%20measure%20advances.%20Litigation%20would%20be%20protracted%20and%20expensive%2C%20and%20it%20would%20generate%20sustained%20negative%20attention%20to%20California's%20business%20climate.%20The%20prudent%20course%20is%20to%20prevent%20this%20constitutionally%20defective%20measure%20from%20reaching%20the%20ballot.%20We%20respectfully%20ask%20that%20you%20discourage%20signature%20gathering%2C%20oppose%20qualification%2C%20and%20if%20necessary%2C%20campaign%20against%20passage.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EOur%20clients%20prefer%20to%20remain%20in%20California%20and%20continue%20contributing%20to%20the%20state's%20economy%20and%20civic%20life.%20But%20they%20will%20not%20remain%20if%20subjected%20to%20an%20unconstitutional%20confiscation%20of%20their%20wealth.%20We%20hope%20this%20can%20be%20resolved%20through%20political%20channels%20rather%20than%20through%20years%20of%20contentious%20litigation.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3ERespectfully%2C%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EAlex%20Spiro%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falex-spiro-letter-gavin-newsom-stop-california-wealth-tax-billionaires-2025-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1767041209000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6952d8cf64858d02d2177d48%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falex-spiro-letter-gavin-newsom-stop-california-wealth-tax-billionaires-2025-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20prominent%20lawyer%2C%20who%20has%20represented%20Elon%20Musk%20and%20Jay%20Z%20in%20the%20past%2C%20said%20unnamed%20clients%20would%20flee%20the%20state%20if%20the%20proposal%20passes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jnewsham%40insider.com%20(Jack%20Newsham%2CMadeline%20Berg)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A117%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falex-spiro-letter-gavin-newsom-stop-california-wealth-tax-billionaires-2025-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Stranger%20Things%205%E2%80%99%20Gets%20Review%20Bombed%20as%20Will%E2%80%99s%20Coming%20Out%20Becomes%20Worst-Rated%20Episode%20on%20IMDb%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1767040210000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F12%2FStrangerThings_S5_0509_R.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22