with%20Ukraine%20heavily%20relying%20on%20them%20as%20it%20faces%20regular%20shortages%20of%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eweapons%2C%20ammo%2C%20and%20manpower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrones%20give%20Ukraine%20a%20key%20advantage%20because%20they%20can%20be%20produced%20domestically%20and%20at%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20many%20traditional%20weapons%2C%20creating%20an%20asymmetric%20threat%20to%20expensive%20assets%20such%20as%20Black%20Sea%20Fleet%20warships%20or%20T-90%20tanks%20on%20the%20battlefield.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EUkraine%E2%80%99s%20defense%20minister%20said%20last%20week%20that%20the%20armed%20forces%20expect%20to%20receive%20nearly%203%20million%20FPV%20drones%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20most%20of%20them%20made%20at%20home%20%E2%80%94%20though%20Russia%20is%20also%20rapidly%20developing%20and%20fielding%20similar%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorried%20about%20the%20potential%20for%20a%20future%20conflict%20with%20Russia%2C%20much%20of%20the%20West%20is%20closely%20watching%20Ukraine's%20tactics%20and%20new%20war%20tech.%20Naval%20drones%20are%20one%20of%20the%20innovations%20Ukraine%20has%20said%20it%20is%20willing%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-ready-export-sea-drones-hurt-russia-black-sea-fleet-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eexport%20to%20partner%20nations%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENATO%20allies%20and%20defense%20companies%20are%20working%20on%20the%20technology%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20Baltic%20Sea%2C%20which%20is%20shared%20by%20a%20host%20of%20NATO%20members%20and%20Russia.%20The%20US%20military%20is%20also%20exploring%20the%20potential%20of%20these%20weapon%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20Gen.%20Christopher%20Cavoli%2C%20NATO's%20supreme%20allied%20commander%20in%20Europe%2C%20called%20the%20way%20that%20Ukraine%20was%20able%20to%20move%20Russia's%20navy%20with%20drones%20an%20%26quot%3Barbiter%20of%20things%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20that